n't been tampered with mid-transit or on the mirror server. For the latest vulnerability intelligence, visit:https://cvedatabase.com#CVE#InfoSec#CyberSecurity#SupplyChain#AppSec"], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['cvedatabase.com'], 'email-addr': ['cvedatabase@techhub.social']}}, {'title': '⚠️ EXECUTIVE ALERT: CVE-2026-39808 enables OS command injection on Fortinet FortiSandbox. With active exploitation confirmed, this is a Tier 1 risk to your infrastructure. Is your organization prepared to defend its perimeter? Get the board-ready risk assessment and playbook today. https://thecybermind.co/7ou0#CISO #InfoSec', 'publication_date': 'Mon, 20 Jul 2026 22:42:04 +0000', 'source': 'https://mastodon.social/@thecybermind/116954649426452026', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': ['EXECUTIVE ALERT: CVE-2026-39808 enables OS command injection on Fortinet FortiSandbox. With active exploitation confirmed, this is a Tier 1 risk to your infrastructure. Is your organization prepared to defend its perimeter? Get the board-ready risk assessment and playbook today.https://thecybermind.co/7ou0'], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['thecybermind.co'], 'email-addr': ['thecybermind@mastodon.social'], 'vulnerability': ['CVE-2026-39808']}}, {'title': 'CVE-2026-63728 - Gitleaks Secret Exfiltration via Non-Hermetic Sprig Template Functions in Report Template Feature', 'publication_date': 'Tue, 21 Jul 2026 00:17:48 +0000', 'source': 'https://cvefeed.io/vuln/detail/CVE-2026-63728', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': ['Gitleaks prior to 8.30.1 contains a template injection vulnerability that allows attackers who can supply or influence report templates to read arbitrary environment variables and exfiltrate sensitive data by leveraging non-hermetic Sprig template functions. Attackers can craft malicious report templates using the env, expandenv, and getHostByName functions to extract credentials, tokens, and API keys from the host process and exfiltrate them through DNS queries, including secrets discovered during the scan itself.', 'The following products are affected byCVE-2026-63728vulnerability. Even ifcvefeed.iois aware of the exact versions of the products that are affected, the information is not represented in the table below.', 'Common Attack Pattern Enumeration and Classification (CAPEC) stores attack patterns, which are descriptions of the common attributes and approaches employed by adversaries to exploit theCVE-2026-63728weaknesses.', 'We scan GitHub repositories to detect new proof-of-concept exploits. Following list is a collection of public exploits and proof-of-concepts, which have been published on GitHub (sorted by the most recently updated).', "Vulnerability history details can be useful for understanding the evolution of a vulnerability, and for identifying the most recent changes that may impact the vulnerability's severity, exploitability, or other characteristics."], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['cvefeed.io'], 'email-addr': ['disclosure@vulncheck.com'], 'file': [{'hash_type': 'SHA-1', 'values': ['83d9cd684c87d95d656c1458ef04895a7f1cbd8e']}], 'url': ['http://www.vulncheck.com/advisories/gitleaks-secret-exfiltration-via-non-hermetic-sprig-template-functions-in-report-template-feature', 'https://fatihhcelik.github.io/posts/gitleaks-abusing-sprig-for-exfiltration/#the-fix', 'https://github.com/gitleaks/gitleaks', 'https://github.com/gitleaks/gitleaks/commit/83d9cd684c87d95d656c1458ef04895a7f1cbd8e', 'https://www.vulncheck.com/advisories/gitleaks-secret-exfiltration-via-non-hermetic-sprig-template-functions-in-report-template-feature'], 'vulnerability': ['CVE-2026-63728']}}, {'title': 'CVE-2026-64625 - AVideo before 29.0 OS Command Injection via execAsync', 'publication_date': 'Mon, 20 Jul 2026 22:17:18 +0000', 'source': 'https://cvefeed.io/vuln/detail/CVE-2026-64625', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': ['AVideo before 29.0 contains an incomplete fix for CVE-2026-45578 where execAsync() re-wraps